################################################################################
# Notes:
#
# 1. Domain Configuration:
#    - Replace "your-domain.com" with your actual domain
#    - Replace email address in global options
#    - Ensure DNS A/AAAA records point to your server
#
# 2. SSL Certificates:
#    - Caddy automatically obtains Let's Encrypt certificates
#    - Certificates are stored in Caddy's data directory
#    - Auto-renewal happens automatically
#    - First run might take a few seconds to obtain certs
#
# 3. Path Configuration:
#    - Update "/opt/deepspace" to your actual deployment path
#    - Ensure paths match your PM2 ecosystem.config.js
#
# 4. Firewall Rules:
#    - Open port 80 (HTTP) - for Let's Encrypt validation
#    - Open port 443 (HTTPS) - for secure traffic
#    - Keep port 3000 (backend) closed to external traffic
#
# 5. Testing:
#    - Validate config: caddy validate --config Caddyfile
#    - Test locally: caddy run --config Caddyfile
#    - Check logs: tail -f /var/log/caddy/*.log
#
# 6. Security:
#    - Enable HSTS header after SSL is confirmed working
#    - Adjust CSP based on your actual content sources
#    - Review and tighten CORS policies for production
#    - Consider adding rate limiting for API endpoints
#
# 7. Performance:
#    - Caddy automatically enables HTTP/2 and HTTP/3
#    - Gzip and Brotli compression enabled
#    - Static file caching configured
#    - Precompressed file support enabled
#
# 8. Monitoring:
#    - Access logs: /var/log/caddy/deepspace-access.log
#    - Backend health: /api/health
#    - Caddy metrics available via admin API (if enabled)
################################################################################
